Danganronpa: Prospective Despair
Sector B (KG) / cafeteria
Astrea of the Stars 14-Aug-21 06:55 PM
WARNING: THIS PLACE IS LOCKED AT NIGHT TIME. A standard cafeteria... or, well, as standard as a bunker's cafeteria can be. It's a huge room, with the metal that makes up the walls and ceilings being a dark gray, though the lightning helps somewhat offset the dreariness. Of course there are plenty of tables here - probably enough for a whole mid-sized school. Interestingly enough, the tables here seem to be from schools, too. They're long tables, with them being able to be linked together, and with the seats being more benches than individual sitting places. It works just fine, honestly - though some of the tables look like they've gone through a lot of usage even before coming here. Towards the end of this area is a little section for a buffet - how nice. It seems to be restocked per the typical times for breakfast, lunch, and dinner. Breakfast tends to have mire breakfasty items, like eggs and sausages, while lunch and dinner share items and tend to be typical Japanese food (listing all of them out would be a pain - do a Google search, it's honestly kind of interesting). The food quality is... decent. Certainly passable, though nothing special. At the very end of the place are doors to the #kitchen. Yes, it means this place and the kitchen lock down at night time. It is what it is.
